 0648: """                     Contains following functions

 0656: """                     Vector definition conventions
 0657: The displacement vector between two particles i, and j is defined as:
 0658:                                 uij = rj - ri
 0659: where the ri and rj are position vectors. Thus, force vectors for pair
 0660: potentials are defined as
 0661:                                 fi = -g * uji
 0662:                                 fj = -g * uij
 0663: where g is the gradient and uij = -uij.
 0664:

        #if ((defined(__APPLE__) || defined(__OSX__)) && (defined(__GNUC__) && (__GNUC__ > 2 || (__GNUC__ == 2 && (__GNUC_MINOR__ > 95)))))
            #undef likely
            #undef unlikely
            #define likely(x)   __builtin_expect(!!(x), 1)
            #define unlikely(x) __builtin_expect(!!(x), 0)
        #endif
      }
